# Anthropic API key used client-side via Vite.
# WARNING: This key will be bundled into the browser JS.
# Rotate the key regularly and restrict it by allowed origins in the Anthropic dashboard.
# For production workloads, replace with a server-side proxy (e.g. an Azure Function in api/).
#
# Local development:
#   Copy this file to .env.local and replace the placeholder with your real key.
#   Never commit .env.local to version control.
#
# Azure Static Web Apps deployment:
#   Store the key as a GitHub repository secret named VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.
#   The deploy workflow automatically injects it at build time.
#   Go to: GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret.
#
# Note: the variable must be prefixed with VITE_ because this project uses Vite.
# (REACT_APP_* prefixes are for Create React App projects and will NOT work here.)
VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
